{"title": "Card", "description": "The \u2018Card\u2019 in question is Edward Henry Machin - His mother called him \u2018Denry\u2019. This light-hearted story is of his rise from humble beginnings as the son of a washerwoman and sempstress in the last quarter of the nineteenth century, in the pottery towns (which Arnold Bennett christened \u2018The Five Towns\u2019) of the English Midlands; how, by his own wits, enterprise and \u2018nerve\u2019 he rose to wealth, married bliss and public recognition as the youngest-ever mayor of his home town.<br /><br />\u201c\u2019And yet,\u2019 demanded Councillor Barlow, \u2018what\u2019s he done? What great cause is he identified with?<br />\u2019\u2018He\u2019s identified,\u2019 said the speaker, \u2018with the great cause of cheering us all up\u2019.\u201d (summary by Andy Minter)", "duration": 28701, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "263", "name": "Arnold Bennett"}], "coverArt": "http://archive.org/download/the_card_librivox/Card_1105.jpg", "copyright_year": "1910", "genres": ["General Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Andy Minter (1934-2017)"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Andy Minter (1934-2017)"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Kristin LeMoine"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1 \u2013 The Dance", "readers": [152], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_card_librivox/the_card_01_bennett_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2345}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2 \u2013 The Widow Hullin\u2019s House", "readers": [152], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_card_librivox/the_card_02_bennett_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2463}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 3 \u2013 The Pantechnicol", "readers": [152], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_card_librivox/the_card_03_bennett_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2669}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 4 \u2013 The Wrecking of a Life", "readers": [152], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_card_librivox/the_card_04_benne